               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the donors; name of the protagonist (both Libanos and Mäṭaˤ); the word sälam; groups of line on the incipit page of Text I; incipits of some subsections in Text I; incipit of each miracle in Text II; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- For the Texts of Gädlä Libanos, Täʾamrä Libanos and Mälkǝʾa Libanos compare them to the edited version: A. BAUSI, La «Vita» e i «miracoli» di Libānos, Lovanii 2003 (CSCO 595, 596 [SAe 105, 106]).</note>
                     <note>- Text II is preceded by a short praise (on fol. 47va, ls. 3-19) in honour of the Saint. It is written in a smaller script but most probably by the same hand.</note>
                     <note>- In the incipits of the Miracles (Text II), both names of the protagonist (Libanos and Mäṭaˤ) are alternatively used.</note>
                     <note>Lacuna between Text II and Text III (fol. 62vb, ls. 4-9).</note>
                     <note>- In Text III, as compared to the edited version (cp. A. BAUSI, La «Vita» e i «miracoli» di Libānos, Lovanii 2003a (CSCO 595, 596 [SAe 105, 106]),<ref type="mss" corresp="ES206212">206-212</ref>[text] and<ref type="mss" corresp="ES119122">119-122</ref>[tr.]), one strophe at the end is missing.</note>
                     <note>- The ultimate portion of Text III is written on the first (unruled) leaf of quire B, probably by the hand different from that of the main text (hand a).</note>
                     <note>- A ruled line at the bottom was not used by the scribe, on fols. 3r-10v, 35r-36v.</note>
                     <note>- The rubrication is mostly carried out in reddish-brown; the ink used for the names of the donors is of somewhat different tones (e.g., cp. Wäldä Mikaʾel, fol. 36ra, l.17, and Zä-Wäldä Maryam, fol. 55vb, l.3).</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
